content.text:
**Docs Proposal**
- Title: Workspace Scanning + Diff Viewer PoC
- Purpose: Demonstrate connecting a local workspace, hashing files via worker, computing ChangeSet, and loading workspace sessions; clarify IDs used to correlate session events.
- Audience: Users on Chromium-based browsers; Firefox/Safari see documented fallback.
- Sections:
  - Overview and prerequisites (HTTPS origin, Chromium FS Access availability).
  - Permissions and security (user activation, read vs readwrite, revocation UX).
  - Data model: file hash records and ChangeSet; session event IDs.
  - User flows: Connect Workspace → Rescan → View Changed Files → Load Workspace Session → Open Diff.
  - Fallbacks: drag-and-drop handles; manual .zip import when FS Access is not available.
  - Privacy: local-only IndexedDB storage of paths + SHA-256; clearing site data removes it.
  - References: MDN pages and idb README (see Sources).

**PoC (drop-in demo snippet)**
- Where: docs page snippet or a sandbox route; built on APIs already in this repo.
- Minimal TypeScript example (uses shipped helpers):

```ts
// UI wires
const btnConnect = document.getElementById('connect')!;
const btnRescan = document.getElementById('rescan')!;
const list = document.getElementById('changes')!;
const status = document.getElementById('status')!;

// App helpers from this repo
import { startFileSystemScanFromHandle } from '../src/utils/fs-scanner';
import { listHashes } from '../src/utils/session-db';
import { buildChangeSet } from '../src/scanner/diffIndex';

let workspace: FileSystemDirectoryHandle | null = null;

btnConnect.onclick = async () => {
  try {
    // Requires Chromium + user activation
    // @ts-ignore experimental
    workspace = await (window as any).showDirectoryPicker?.({ id: 'workspace', mode: 'read' });
    status.textContent = workspace ? `Connected: ${workspace.name}` : 'No folder selected';
  } catch {
    status.textContent = 'Permission denied or not supported';
  }
};

btnRescan.onclick = async () => {
  if (!workspace) return;
  status.textContent = 'Scanning…';
  const before = await listHashes();

  const runner = startFileSystemScanFromHandle(workspace);
  const off = runner.onProgress((p) => (status.textContent = `Indexing: ${p}`));

  await new Promise<void>((resolve) => {
    const onMsg = (e: MessageEvent) => {
      if (e.data === 'done' || e.data === 'aborted') {
        runner.worker.removeEventListener('message', onMsg as any);
        off();
        resolve();
      }
    };
    runner.worker.addEventListener('message', onMsg as any);
  });

  const after = await listHashes();
  const cs = buildChangeSet(before, after);

  status.textContent = `Added ${cs.added} • Modified ${cs.modified} • Deleted ${cs.deleted}`;
  list.innerHTML = '';
  for (const it of cs.items) {
    const li = document.createElement('li');
    li.textContent = `[${it.type}] ${it.path}`;
    list.appendChild(li);
  }
};

